article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 87, Upper Iowa University 59
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Avery Smith scored 17 of his 22 points in the second half to lead Wisconsin-Milwaukee to an 87-59 victory over Upper Iowa Wednesday night in the Panthers' home opener. Deonte Roberts added 12 points, James Eayrs 11 and Ricky Franklin 10 for Milwaukee (3-1). The victory kept coach Rob Jeter undefeated in four home openers. Division II Upper Iowa (0-2 )was led by Mark Lafrenz with 11 points. The Panthers took control early with an 11-4 run that put them up 15-8. Tone Boyle began the decisive scoring spurt with a 3-point play with 14:54 to snap a 4-4 tie and James Eayrs ended it with a 3-pointer. Milwaukee never lost the lead after that.
